Other objects and advantages of the present invention will be apparent to those skilled in the art upon reading the following detailed description and upon reference to the drawings in which:


FIG. 1 is a perspective view of a first preferred embodiment of a micromirror device of the present invention;


FIGS. 2A-2C are fragmentary side views showing an electromagnetic field between a first conductive coil and a second conductive coil that causes axial rotation of the micromirror device of the present invention;


FIG. 3 is a side view of the micromirror device illustrating the etching of a recess into a semiconductor wafer in accordance with the present invention;


FIGS. 4A and 4B are a top view and side view, respectively, of the micromirror device illustrating the formation of a primary magnetic field source in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 5 is a side view of the micromirror device illustrating the formation of a magnetic ring in accordance with the present invention;


FIGS. 6-8 are views of the micromirror device illustrating the formation a platform in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 9 is a top view of an alternative embodiment of a micromirror device which allows for three-dimensional platform motion;


FIG. 10 is a side view of the micromirror device illustrating backside fabrication in accordance with the present invention; and


FIG. 11 is a perspective view of a second alternate embodiment of a micromirror device in accordance with the present invention.
